This notebook is created on 26 of Dec 2021 to plot correlation between different scorers.¶

It is corrected on 20th of Jan, 2022.

They had a first round of scoring with Sandra, Martin, Sinem, Oscar, and Deniz on only two sample group of Control and MV+LPS. The second round was the same people but they scored all 5 sample groups. And the point is these five people scored the images in 0-8 range. However, the gold-standard paper that Iran compares their work to that is in the range of 0-2. So, Iran made the transformation of these scores from 0-8 to 0-2. Then, They had new scorers called Isabel, Pablo, Pieter, Laura, Nika, och Darcy. They scored the same images in the range of 0-2 originally. Then only three of these people (Isabel, Nika, and Darcy) repeat their scoring in the range of 0-8 one or two month later. Iran wanted me to plot the correlation between the scores of first 5 people with the second 6 people where both scores are in range of 0-2 (the scores of first group transformed to 0-2 and the second group of six people were originally in the range of 0-2.). And also the agreement between the scores of three people (Isable, Nika, and Darcy) which is done with one or two month time in between and the first time was in range of 0-2 and the second time in range of 0-8.

Summary of the scorers, level of expertise, and the range of scores¶

this section is only for plotting the different characteristics of the scores for the first group of 5 people¶

The min, max, std, and median of the data is plotted over all sample groups and for each sample group separately

Data characteristics¶

Here, I have changed the mean to median according what Iran said based on this paper.¶

https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pmc/articles/PMC3795863/

Each field scored and a mean (i.e. average) score assigned for the whole tissue of that animal. The problem with this approach is that the mean represents a measure of central tendency that is only appropriate for interval and ratio data. For ordinal data, the median is the most appropriate measure for central tendency. This statistical axiom is not without some controversy and it is not within the scope of this paper to resolve it.

Scores by six people in range of 0-2¶

Iran changed the range of total score to 0-1 and I had to do the same for other scores by dividing them to 56.

It is not a transformation. It is the total decision for the lung injury. if all the features (0-2) is 2 then the total is 1. It means positive to lung injury.¶

Dividing each feature to 4 was not correct. I only can do it for the total score.¶

The formula for converting the total score to 0-1 is =0.2a+0.14b+0.07c+0.07d+0.02*e

The sum of weights is 0.5.

When all features are 2 then it shows maximum injury which is 1.

feature a is the most important feature, then b. c and d equally and then e

Second group did not have any scores for f, and g features.¶

That is why:

Because they noted that in pigs they can identify the (e.g.,'hemorrage') as an important feature, while on the standard 0-2, they don't see it important, so it had a low power.

It is because the 0-2 standard was first developed for mice. And mice don't have hemorrage, but then researchers started to use this system for pigs. Then they found false results and this is the importance of Iran's system. They are giving importance to the aspects that are more relevant in pigs.
